byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Adriana Ramić

abstract: On the brink of actual voting, the party that preached of unity to defeat President Trump finds itself very divided.
snippet: On the brink of actual voting, the party that preached of unity to defeat President Trump finds itself very divided.

abstract: In the real world, political primaries are looming, impeachment is ongoing and heavy news never seems to stop. But during commercial breaks in the Super Bowl, advertisers did their best to serve up an antidote heavily spiked with fun.
snippet: In the real world, political primaries are looming, impeachment is ongoing and heavy news never seems to stop. But during commercial breaks in the Super Bowl, advertisers did their best to serve up an antidote heavily spiked with fun.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — In the real world, political primaries are looming, impeachment is ongoing and heavy news never seems to stop. But during commercial breaks in the Super Bowl, advertisers did their best to serve up an antidote heavily spiked with fun.
headline_main: Super Bowl Ads Dialed Up Fun as an Antidote to Politics
headline_print_headline: Super Bowl Ads Dialed Up Fun as an Antidote to Politics

headline_print_headline: Acquittal Clear, Trump Celebrates, Then Fulminates Against Bloomberg

abstract: Bernie Sanders is increasingly seen as the candidate on the rise. But the Iowa contest is unusually jumbled, and several candidates have realistic hopes for a sudden burst of momentum.
snippet: Bernie Sanders is increasingly seen as the candidate on the rise. But the Iowa contest is unusually jumbled, and several candidates have realistic hopes for a sudden burst of momentum.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The Democratic presidential candidates pleaded with voters in Iowa for their last-minute consideration on Sunday, competing with the Super Bowl for caucusgoers’ attention and straining against an atmosphere of unusual uncertainty and indecision among Democrats ahead of the first-in-the-nation nominating contest.

abstract: In an interview with Sean Hannity of Fox News, President Trump insulted his potential 2020 rivals, lamented impeachment and defended his administration’s coronavirus policies.
snippet: In an interview with Sean Hannity of Fox News, President Trump insulted his potential 2020 rivals, lamented impeachment and defended his administration’s coronavirus policies.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Trump defended a decision that would bar foreign nationals who had recently visited China from entering the United States as his administration continued to assess the growing threat of a coronavirus outbreak.

abstract: In a pair of appearances on college campuses, Senator Elizabeth Warren remained laser-focused on a central theme of her candidacy.
snippet: In a pair of appearances on college campuses, Senator Elizabeth Warren remained laser-focused on a central theme of her candidacy.
lead_paragraph: AMES — In a pair of appearances on college campuses on her final full day of campaigning before the Iowa caucuses, Senator Elizabeth Warren remained laser-focused on a central theme of her candidacy: combating corruption.

abstract: Mr. Trump was interviewed by Sean Hannity during a Super Bowl pregame show.
snippet: Mr. Trump was interviewed by Sean Hannity during a Super Bowl pregame show.
lead_paragraph: The Super Bowl pregame show on Sunday afternoon included what has become a traditional feature for the broadcast: an interview with the president of the United States. This time, it afforded President Trump the opportunity to criticize Democrats vying to be his general election opponent — and offered a preview of what some of his insults might look like in a general election.
headline_main: President Trump recycles insults aimed at Democratic candidates.

abstract: While most of the Democratic presidential candidates were on the ground in Iowa Sunday, a very different clash was unfolding on the air and online — between President Trump and Michael R. Bloomberg.
snippet: While most of the Democratic presidential candidates were on the ground in Iowa Sunday, a very different clash was unfolding on the air and online — between President Trump and Michael R. Bloomberg.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — While most of the Democratic presidential candidates and a platoon of Trump surrogates were on the ground in Iowa Sunday, a very different clash was unfolding on the air and online — between President Trump and Michael R. Bloomberg.
headline_main: Elsewhere, wealthy New Yorkers are feuding.
